This paper is about using Quality-Diversity optimization algorithms to enable robots to autonomously discover a range of behaviors. As such, it is most likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as unsupervised dimensionality reduction, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using computer vision to analyze the robot's behavior, which could place it in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimizing the robot's behavior in a specific environment, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
